    <p>Information about Dr. Lavian's credentials, experience, patents, and publications is provided for reference. Use of such information for professional purposes requires appropriate attribution and permission.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="terms-section">
    <h2>4. Expert Witness Services</h2>

    <h3>Nature of Services</h3>
    <p>Dr. Tal Lavian provides expert witness and litigation support services in telecommunications, networking, data communications, and related technology matters. Services include technical analysis, expert reports, deposition testimony, and trial testimony.</p>

    <h3>Engagement Requirements</h3>
    <p>Expert witness services are provided through formal engagement with law firms or parties represented by counsel. Engagements typically require:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Written engagement agreement or fee arrangement</li>
      <li>Detailed description of technical issues and case scope</li>
      <li>Access to relevant documents and evidence</li>
      <li>Defined timeline and deliverables</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Professional Standards</h3>
    <p>All expert witness services are provided in accordance with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Federal Rules of Civil Procedure and evidence rules</li>
      <li>Professional ethics and standards</li>
      <li>Court rules and procedures in applicable jurisdictions</li>
      <li>Attorney-client privilege and work product protection</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Expert Opinion</h3>
    <p>Expert opinions are based on Dr. Lavian's professional knowledge, analysis of facts and evidence, industry standards, and technical principles. Opinions are subject to applicable Daubert or similar standards for expert testimony admissibility.</p>
  </div>

